children.text: The wall insulation batts have not been installed in the wall corners, which will be reducing the effectiveness of the thermal performance.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3999 Thermal Insulation of Dwellings - Bulk Insulation - Installation Requirements, states in section 5.3.4.1 that ‘
Where there is a narrow gap between non-standard stud spacing’s this shall be filled with the specified insulation thickness as shown in Figure 5.4.3.1.2’ .
These missing batts in the wall junctions must be properly installed to ensure thermal performance.
